[[File:Berehap-1484675823.jpeg|thumb|A meal with berenklauw]]

A '''berenklauw''' ('''Bear's claw''' in English) or '''spoetnik''' ('''[[Sputnik 1|Sputnik]]''' in English) is a deep-fried [[fast food]] snack from the [[Netherlands]]. It consists of a sliced [[meatball]] and fried [[onion|onion rings]] on a wooden [[skewer]], smothered in [[peanut sauce]] (also known as [[satay]] sauce) which originated in the [[Indonesian cuisine]]. The snack is also served with "Zigeunersaus" (literally translated: Gypsy-sauce), should one not like satay sauce. Sometimes, [[pineapple]] or [[bell pepper]] are used as well as onion rings.

