{{Infobox union | name = IF Metall | country = [[Sweden]] | affiliation = [[Swedish Trade Union Confederation|LO]] | members = 325,000 | image = [[Image:IFMETALL logo.png]] | founded = {{Start date|2006|01|01|df=yes}} | predecessor = [[Swedish Industrial Union]] and [[Swedish Metalworkers' Union]] | head = Marie Nilsson | office = [[Stockholm]], Sweden | website = [http://www.ifmetall.se/ www.ifmetall.se] }}
'''IF Metall''' is a [[trade union]] in [[Sweden]]. It was formed in a 2006 merger between the [[Swedish Industrial Union]] (Industrifacket) and the [[Swedish Metalworkers' Union]] (Metall). Its roots in Metall trace back to 1888.
IF Metall represents around 325,000 workers in around 11,600 workplaces. 22% are women, 15% are under 30 years of age and around 25% are of foreign background.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ifmetall.se/ifmetall/home/content.nsf/aget?openagent&key=smabba_fakta_1295002910106 |title=Snabbfakta om förbundet |work=IF Metall |date=14 February 2014 |accessdate=2 March 2014 |language=sv |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140302231126/https://www.ifmetall.se/ifmetall/home/content.nsf/aget?openagent&key=smabba_fakta_1295002910106 |archivedate=2 March 2014 |df= }}</ref> in a variety of sectors, including:
* mechanical engineering and the [[plastics industry]] * the [[building material]] industry * the [[mining]] sector * the [[Ferrous metallurgy|ironworks]] sector * the [[textile industry]], including [[clothing]] * [[automobile repair shop]]s * including disabled workers doing similar tasks within government sponsored projects, including Samhall
IF Metall is the second largest affiliate of the [[Swedish Trade Union Confederation]].
==List of chairmen== * [[Stefan Löfven]], 2006–2012 * Anders Ferbe, 2012–2017 * Marie Nilsson, 2017-present
