The '''Liberation Tower''' ({{lang-ro|Turnul Dezrobirii Basarabiei}}) was a [[tower]] in [[Chişinău]], [[Bessarabia Governorate|Bessarabia]]. The tower had a height of over {{convert|30|m|ft|0}}. King [[Michael of Romania]], his mother, [[Helen of Greece and Denmark]], and [[Mihai Antonescu]] attended the opening ceremony on November 1, 1942, in [[Ghidighici]]. The tower was destroyed in 1944, after the [[Soviet occupation of Bessarabia and Northern Bukovina|Soviet re-occupation]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.voceabasarabiei.net/stiri/cultura/20359-foto-video-monumentul-turnul-dezrobirii-basarabiei-.html|title=Monumentul "Turnul Dezrobirii Basarabiei"|publisher=[[Vocea Basarabiei]]|language=Romanian|accessdate=2012-02-17}}</ref><ref>Vlad Dumbravă, Turnul dezrobirii Basarabiei de la Ghidighici, Cugetul: Revistă de istorie şi cultură. 1999, Nr. 4, P. 48-50.</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.literaturasiarta.md/pressview.php?l=ro&idc=205&id=2511&zidc=1|title=Turnul Dezrobirii Basarabiei|publisher=[[Literatura şi Arta]]|language=Romanian|accessdate=2012-02-17}}</ref>
